Step 1. Compute the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
 • Debt is all liabilities. Here Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity – Total Owner's Equity = 14214117.02 – 13835266.51 = 378850.51.  
 • Total Assets = 14214117.02.  
 • Debt to Asset Ratio = 378850.51 / 14214117.02 ≈ 0.02664, which when rounded to two decimal places is 0.03.

Step 2. Compute the Gross Profit Margin.  
 • Gross Profit = 1622011.03 and Total Revenue = 2637011.03.  
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 ≈ (1622011.03 / 2637011.03) × 100 ≈ 61.50%.

Step 3. Compute the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
 • Operating Cash Flow (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) = -1028375.55.  
 • Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 378850.51.  
 • Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Total Current Liabilities ≈ -1028375.55 / 378850.51 ≈ -2.71.

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.03",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "61.50%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.71"
  }
}
